[{"publisher": "Amnesforeningen for genusvetenskap", "abstract": "<jats:p>Med inspiration og teknikker lånt fra kussetryk praktiseret af feministiske bevægelser fokuserer værket på synliggørelse af queer genitalier. Med analoge teknikker åbner værket op for måder at lære og genlære sammen om kroppe, fejl og forandringer.</jats:p>", "DOI": "10.55870/tgv.v45i2-3.13948", "type": "journal-article", "title": ["Mit skridt. Eller min testopik, min dick clit, min pik, min minipik, min kæmpeklit, min klit, min clit dick.", "Skridt"], "author": [{"given": "Marie", "family": "Andersen", "sequence": "first", "affiliation": []}], "container-title": ["Tidskrift för genusvetenskap"], "link": [{"URL": "https://publicera.kb.se/tgv/article/download/13948/50824", "content-type": "text/xml", "content-version": "vor", "intended-application": "text-mining"}, {"URL": "https://publicera.kb.se/tgv/article/download/13948/50825", "content-type": "application/pdf", "content-version": "vor", "intended-application": "text-mining"}, {"URL": "https://publicera.kb.se/tgv/article/download/13948/50825", "content-type": "unspecified", "content-version": "vor", "intended-application": "similarity-checking"}], "URL": "https://doi.org/10.55870/tgv.v45i2-3.13948", "published": {"date-parts": [[2025, 12, 30]]}}, {"publisher": "Copernicus GmbH", "DOI": "10.5194/egusphere-2025-2928-ac3", "type": "peer-review", "title": ["Reply on RC1"], "author": [{"ORCID": "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1519-5069", "authenticated-orcid": false, "given": "Min", "family": "Min", "sequence": "first", "affiliation": []}], "URL": "https://doi.org/10.5194/egusphere-2025-2928-ac3", "published": {"date-parts": [[2025, 10, 16]]}}, {"publisher": "Copernicus GmbH", "DOI": "10.5194/egusphere-2025-2928-ac1", "type": "peer-review", "title": ["Reply on RC3"], "author": [{"ORCID": "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1519-5069", "authenticated-orcid": false, "given": "Min", "family": "Min", "sequence": "first", "affiliation": []}], "URL": "https://doi.org/10.5194/egusphere-2025-2928-ac1", "published": {"date-parts": [[2025, 10, 16]]}}, {"publisher": "Copernicus GmbH", "DOI": "10.5194/egusphere-2025-2928-ac2", "type": "peer-review", "title": ["Reply on RC2"], "author": [{"ORCID": "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1519-5069", "authenticated-orcid": false, "given": "Min", "family": "Min", "sequence": "first", "affiliation": []}], "URL": "https://doi.org/10.5194/egusphere-2025-2928-ac2", "published": {"date-parts": [[2025, 10, 16]]}}, {"publisher": "Center for Open Science", "abstract": "<p>We attempted to replicate Study 1 from Gino and Bazerman (2009), which reported that people are more likely to accept the unethical behavior of others if it develops gradually (slippery slope) rather than all at once (abrupt change). Using two Qualtrics surveys conducted with participants from Prolific, we investigated approval rates for estimates based on gradual versus abrupt changes in scenarios where participants had to estimate varying values of pennies in jars. Our key results fail to replicate those of Gino and Bazerman. We obtained no significant differences in approval rates between the two conditions. Thus, this replication’s key preregistered analyses fail to reaffirm the original study’s result.</p>", "DOI": "10.31234/osf.io/a6qnk_v1", "type": "posted-content", "title": ["Replication of Gino and Bazerman (2009, Study 1)"], "author": [{"given": "Min Min Min", "family": "Fong", "sequence": "first", "affiliation": [{"id": [{"id": "https://ror.org/01an7q238", "id-type": "ROR", "asserted-by": "publisher"}], "name": "University of California, Berkeley"}]}, {"given": "Megan", "family": "Lin", "sequence": "additional", "affiliation": [{"id": [{"id": "https://ror.org/01an7q238", "id-type": "ROR", "asserted-by": "publisher"}], "name": "University of California, Berkeley"}]}, {"given": "Youyou", "family": "Xu", "sequence": "additional", "affiliation": [{"id": [{"id": "https://ror.org/01an7q238", "id-type": "ROR", "asserted-by": "publisher"}], "name": "University of California, Berkeley"}]}, {"given": "Don A", "family": "Moore", "sequence": "additional", "affiliation": []}, {"given": "max", "family": "bazerman", "sequence": "additional", "affiliation": []}], "URL": "https://doi.org/10.31234/osf.io/a6qnk_v1", "published": {"date-parts": [[2025, 2, 24]]}}]